The paper deals with a market-based approach to mobile data trading, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of prospect theory from behavioral economics suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computational economics (cs.CE). The algorithm design aspect of the paper may also place it under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the optimization problem and analysis of the objective function may also suggest the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
